        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">A federal judge has barred Elon Musk and his Department of Government Efficiency (DOGE) team from accessing <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-07-02-2025-h2-3-us-treasury-payment-data" target="_blank">US treasury payments data</a>. A lawsuit filed by representatives of government employees and retirees argued that sharing such data with Musk’s team would violate federal privacy protections.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.5">The case adds to the growing scrutiny of Musk’s involvement in government affairs. The billionaire claimed that his team was rapidly shutting down “illegal” treasury remittances. Critics have alleged that DOGE is bypassing legal protections and intimidating government workers.
          </p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
