            <strong>🇪🇺 European stocks hit record highs as earnings boost investor confidence</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">European stocks hit <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-07-02-2025-wn1-4-record-highs" target="_blank">record highs</a> on Thursday. The Stoxx 600 climbed 1.2%, driven by strong corporate earnings and optimism around resolving trade tensions with the US. The FTSE 100 also gained 1.2% after the Bank of England cut interest rates to a 19-month low.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The rally in European equities came as investors shifted focus away from high-flying US AI companies. The fourth-quarter corporate earnings season exceeded analyst expectations. Danish shipping giant A.P. Moller-Maersk announced a $2 billion share buyback causing a surge in shares. The MSCI Europe firms posted 0.3% growth year-on-year.
