          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Luxury logistics firm Ferrari Group Plc is set to raise <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #6b705c; color: black;" href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-07-02-2025-wn2-5-212-million-in-ipo" target="_blank">$212.7 million in an IPO</a> in Amsterdam. If everything goes as planned, this would mark Europe’s first major listing of the year. The Deiana family is offering 25% of their stake, which amounts to about 22.8 million shares.
        </p>
        <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          Ferrari Group specializes in transporting and handling customs services for luxury goods. The company posted revenue of €333 million in 2023. Investors will keenly observe the IPO as this would be a potential indicator of current European market sentiment following a volatile 2024.
